What you need to know:  Guardiola's side head to Madrid with a slender 4-3 advantage after last week's thrilling first leg at the Etihad StadiumGuardiola has never been cowed by the prospect of facing Real on their own turf, winning six times and losing just once in nine visits with City, Barcelona and Bayern MunichCity have already won at the Bernabeu in the Guardiola era, securing a 2-1 triumph in the Champions League last 16 first leg two years ago on route to eliminating the Spanish club